## During combat encounters...
You shape the fight by controlling space and timing. You bind enemies, punish careless movement, and force opponents to act on your terms. Your power comes from preparation, positioning, and threatening enemy mobility.

## During social encounters...
You read people through details they do not realize they reveal. Repairs, posture, habits, and wear all tell stories. You speak carefully and precisely, and when needed, you apply subtle pressure rather than overt threats.

## While exploring...
You secure paths, reinforce gear, and prepare contingencies before danger appears. Traps, hazards, and sudden movement are less threatening when you have already planned how to limit them.

## In downtime...
You mend, modify, and experiment. Armor, clothing, tools, and threads become testbeds for new techniques. Your craft improves through constant refinement rather than inspiration.

## You Might...
* Treat preparation as a form of offense  
* Prefer control and certainty over improvisation  
* View movement and positioning as problems to be solved  

## Others Probably...
* Underestimate you until they are restrained  
* Find your patience unsettling  
* Notice that fights seem calmer when you are involved  

