### Forced Movement and Teleportation

Forced movement does not trigger threads.

If an anchor teleports, leaves the plane, or otherwise moves without traversing intervening space, the thread immediately unravels.

Threads do not prevent teleportation unless an ability explicitly states otherwise.

### Multiple Threads

If a creature encounters multiple threads during a single movement, each thread can trigger independently, subject to any limits imposed by your abilities.

item(
# Needle Throw ((+Needle Throw)) :a:
-
; attack, finesse, ranged, manipulate

**Range** 20 feet, increment 20 feet

Make a ranged Strike with a needle at an unoccupied square, an unattended object, or a held object you can clearly target. On a hit, you create or extend a thread anchored at the struck square or object, choosing the thread’s effect slot when it is created. The thread’s length cannot exceed your maximum thread length and it counts against your maximum number of threads.

If the target is an ordinary unattended object or an empty square with no listed AC, use DC 13 for this Strike. For other targets without a listed AC, use the DC by level.

**Tether Weave** If you have selected the Tether Weave style, you can target a creature with Needle Throw. On a hit, you create or extend a thread anchored at that creature, and the other end must be anchored to you, creating a tether. You are always the anchor for your end of a tether, and it occupies your space as you move. A creature can have only one tether to you at a time unless an ability states otherwise. A tether to a willing creature is protective, and a tether to an unwilling creature is hostile. A tether to an unwilling ally has no protective effects.

Creating or extending a thread with this action uses your Combat Seamstress class DC for any required saves or checks related to that thread.
